== Shrines Dedicated to Ōmiyanome == [[File:Omiya-inari-jinja (Kyoto, Kyoto).JPG|thumb|200px|right|Ōmiya Hime Inari Shrine ({{ill|Kyoto|ja|京都市|qq=draft|qq=draft}})]] [[File:Omiyame-jinja, haiden.jpg|thumb|200px|right|{{ill|Ōmiyanome Shrine|ja|大宮売神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Kyōtango City)]] Ōmiya Hime Inari Shrine, located near the former site of the {{ill|Jingikan|ja|神祇官|1=Department of Divinities|blank=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in {{ill|Kyoto|ja|京都市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and {{ill|Ōmiyanome Shrine|ja|大宮売神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in {{ill|Kyōtango|ja|京丹後市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the only {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|qq=draft}} bearing the name "Ōmiyanome," venerate her as the primary deity. Additionally, she is worshiped at {{ill|Fushimi Inari-taisha|ja|伏見稲荷大社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and other {{ill|Inari Shrines|ja|稲荷神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} across Japan as a subordinate deity of Ukanomitama.
