Ōmiya Hime Inari Shrine, located near the former site of the {{ill|Jingikan|ja|神祇官|1=Department of Divinities|blank=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jingikan|13=User:Immanuelle/Department of Divinities|qq=}} in {{ill|Kyoto|ja|京都市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kyoto|qq=}}, and {{ill|Ōmiya Shrine|lt=Ōmiya Shrine|lt=Ōmiyanome Shrine|ja|大宮売神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōmiyanome Shrine|qq=}} in {{ill|Kyōtango|ja|京丹後市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kyōtango|qq=}}, the only {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|qq=}} bearing the name "Ōmiyanome," venerate her as the primary deity. Additionally, she is worshiped at {{ill|Fushimi Inari-taisha|ja|伏見稲荷大社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fushimi Inari-taisha|qq=}} and other {{ill|Inari Shrines|ja|稲荷神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Inari Shrines|qq=}} across Japan as a subordinate deity of Ukanomitama.

