<!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me--><!--Ōmiya-no-Me-->

'''Ōmiyanome''' (大宮売) is a [[Shinto]] [[Kami|Deity]]. In the {{ill|Engishiki Jinmyōchō|ja|延喜式神名帳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Engishiki Jinmyōchō|qq=}} and [[:en:Kogo Shūi|Kogo Shūi]], she is written as '''Ōmiyanome no Kami''' (大宮売神), while at [[:en:Fushimi Inari-taisha|Fushimi Inari-taisha]], she is referred to as '''Ōmiyanome no Ōkami''' (大宮能売大神).<ref name=gosaijin>{{Cite web|language=ja|url=http://inari.jp/about/saijin/|author=伏見稲荷大社 |title=伏見稲荷大社とは -ご祭神|accessdate=2016-04-15}}</ref> She is a goddess who protects the peace of [[:en:Palace|palaces]].<ref name=inariookami>稲田智宏「稲荷大神五柱とは何か」『稲荷大神』、戎光祥出版、2009th year 。</ref>
== Mythological Descriptions == Ōmiyanome is not mentioned in either the [[:en:Kojiki|Kojiki]] or the [[:en:Nihon Shoki|Nihon Shoki]], but she appears in the [[:en:Kogo Shūi|Kogo Shūi]] as a child of {{ill|Futodama|ja|太玉命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Futodama|qq=}}. She is described as serving as an attendant to [[:en:Amaterasu|Amaterasu Ōmikami]] when the latter moved from the [[:en:Amano-Iwato|Heavenly Rock Cave]] to a new palace. According to the text, she acted as a {{ill|court lady|ja|内侍|1=Naishi (court lady)|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/court lady|13=User:Immanuelle/Naishi (court lady)|qq=}} who facilitated harmony between the emperor and his subjects through beautiful and wise words.
In the {{ill|Ōtono Hōgai Norito|ja|大殿祭祝詞|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōtono Hōgai Norito|qq=}} found in the [[:en:Engishiki|Engishiki]], she is described as a deity who resides in the [[Imperial Palace]] and ensures that the {{ill|Imperial princes|1=Shinnō|ja|親王|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imperial princes|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinnō|qq=}} and court ministers serve faithfully without error.
== Explanation == Ōmiyanome is one of the eight deities venerated by the [[:en:Department of Divinities|Department of Divinities]] for the protection of the [[Emperor of Japan|emperor]].<ref name=inariookami/> She has been described as a personification of the palace or the deification of court ladies. Her role is to mediate and harmonize the relationship between the emperor and his subjects.<ref name=tobe>{{Cite book|author=戸部民夫|title=「日本の神様」がよくわかる本|publisher=PHP研究所|year=2004|isbn=978-4569661155|pages=271–272}}</ref>
As one of the {{ill|Three Deities of Inari|ja|稲荷三神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Three Deities of Inari|qq=}} enshrined at [[:en:Fushimi Inari-taisha|Fushimi Inari-taisha]], she is worshiped as a subordinate deity to [[:en:Ukanomitama|Ukanomitama]], the main deity of the upper shrine.<ref name=inariookami/> Some interpretations suggest that she is a deified [[:en:Miko|miko]] who served the agricultural deity Ukanomitama.<ref name=tobe/> Because of her attributes, she was worshipped as the guardian deity of official markets in [[:en:Heian-kyō|Heian-kyō]], eventually becoming associated with prosperity in business.<ref name=inariookami/>
Additionally, the Edo-period [[:en:Kokugaku|kokugaku]] scholar [[:en:Hirata Atsutane|Hirata Atsutane]] argued in his text "Miyabinokami no Dengi" that the deity {{ill|Okita-no-Kami|lt=Okita-no-Kami|lt=Miyabinokami|ja|宮比神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Miyabinokami|qq=}} of the {{ill|Inner Shrine of Ise|ja|皇大神宮|1=Kōtai Jingū|2=ja|3=皇大神宮|4=zh|5=皇大神宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Inner Shrine of Ise|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōtai Jingū|qq=}} is another name for either Ōmiyanome or [[:en:Ame-no-Uzume|Ame-no-Uzume]]. At shrines like [[:en:Yūtoku Inari Shrine|Yūtoku Inari Shrine]] and {{ill|Shiwa Inari Shrine|ja|志和稲荷神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shiwa Inari Shrine|qq=}}, Ōmiyanome is identified with Ame-no-Uzume and revered as a deity of artistic skill.<ref>{{Cite web|language=ja|url=https://www.yutokusan.jp/about/|title=お祀りする神様|publisher=祐徳稲荷神社|accessdate=2016-04-15}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|language=ja|url=http://www.shiwa-oinarisan.jp/about/|title=志和稲荷神社について|publisher=志和稲荷神社|accessdate=2016-04-16}}</ref>
== Shrines Dedicated to Ōmiyanome == [[File:Omiya-inari-jinja (Kyoto, Kyoto).JPG|thumb|200px|right|Ōmiya Hime Inari Shrine ([[:en:Kyoto|Kyoto]])]] [[File:Omiyame-jinja, haiden.jpg|thumb|200px|right|{{ill|Ōmiya Shrine|lt=Ōmiya Shrine|lt=Ōmiyanome Shrine|ja|大宮売神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōmiyanome Shrine|qq=}} (Kyōtango City)]] Ōmiya Hime Inari Shrine, located near the former site of the [[:en:Department of Divinities|Department of Divinities]] in [[:en:Kyoto|Kyoto]], and {{ill|Ōmiya Shrine|lt=Ōmiya Shrine|lt=Ōmiyanome Shrine|ja|大宮売神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōmiyanome Shrine|qq=}} in [[:en:Kyōtango|Kyōtango]], the only {{ill|Shikinaisha|ja|式内社|1=Shikinaisha|2=ja|3=式内社|qq=draft|1=Shikinaisha|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|13=User:Immanuelle/Shikinaisha|qq=}} bearing the name "Ōmiyanome," venerate her as the primary deity. Additionally, she is worshiped at [[:en:Fushimi Inari-taisha|Fushimi Inari-taisha]] and other [[:en:Inari shrine|Inari Shrines]] across Japan as a subordinate deity of Ukanomitama.
